Family and close friends of Trompies group member Emmanuel “Mjokes” Matsane (55) paid tribute to him at an intimate memorial service yesterday in Newtown, Joburg. The memorial service was organized by his record companies Universal Music South Africa as well as Kalawa Jazmee where he was one of the company directors. ALSO READ | WATCH: MEMORIAL SERVICE OF KWAITO LEGEND MJOKES Mjokes as he was affectionately known died in a car crash on the early hours of Sunday morning after his performance in Meadowlands. Mjokes leaves behind his wife and three children. HERE IS THE GALLERY BELOW:   